# Challenges Faced

One of the biggest lessons from this lab was understanding that **firewall rule order is just as important as the rules themselves**.

If the "DROP" rule is placed before the "ACCEPT" rule, the Load Balancer would also be blocked because iptables processes rules from top to bottom and stops at the first match.

Another important lesson was realizing that firewall rules are stored in memory unless explicitly saved. Enabling the `iptables` service ensures that security policies remain intact even after a system reboot.

