# Real-World Application

This mirrors how production environments secure backend infrastructure.

Rather than exposing application servers directly to users, organizations place them behind reverse proxies or load balancers such as:

* AWS Application Load Balancer (ALB)
* NGINX
* HAProxy
* Traefik

Only these trusted components are permitted to communicate with backend servers, significantly reducing the attack surface and improving overall security.

